HEADWORD: Centralization
<hw>Cen`tral*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>centralisation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of
centralizing, or the state of being centralized; the act or process of
combining or reducing several parts into a whole; <as>as, the
<ex>centralization</ex> of power in the general government; the
<ex>centralization</ex> of commerce in a city</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

